IRS990EZ.PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt: THE CORPORATION IS ORGANIZED EXCLUSIVELY FOR CHARITABLE, EDUCATIONAL AND THE FOSTERING OF NATIONAL/INTERNATIONAL AMATEUR SPORTS COMPETITION PURPOSES WITHIN THE MEANING OF SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE OF 1986, AS AMENDED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE FOLLOWING: A. TO ADVANCE THE SPORT OF FLAT TRACK ROLLER DERBY IN THE CITY OF SEATTLE, NATIONALLY, AND INTERNATIONALLY, MAINTAIN A COMPETITIVE ATHLETIC PROGRAM, PROVIDE QUALITY SPORTS ENTERTAINMENT FOR OUR FANS, AND MAKE A POSITIVE IMPACT IN OUR COMMUNITY, THROUGH COMMUNITY OUTREACH, ATHLETIC TRAINING, NATIONAL AND INTERNATIONAL COMPETITION, AND OPEN OPPORTUNITY FOR ALL WHO ARE WILLING TO COMMIT THEMSELVES TOWARD THE ADVANCEMENT OF THESE GOALS.

ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp.DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt: AS SEATTLE'S PREMIER, MEMBER-OWNED ROLLER DERBY LEAGUE, IT IS OUR MISSION TO MAINTAIN A COMPETITIVE ATHLETIC PROGRAM, PROMOTE THE SPORT OF ROLLER DERBY, PROVIDE QUALITY SPORTS ENTERTAINMENT FOR OUR FANS, AND MAKE A POSITIVE IMPACT IN OUR COMMUNITY.WE FIELD AND SUPPORT COMPETITIVE ROLLER DERBY TEAMS PARTICIPATING IN LOCAL, NATIONAL AND INTERNATIONAL TOURNAMENTS. OUR PROGRAM FOCUSES ON ATHLETE GROWTH AND DEVELOPMENT, TEAM BUILDING, AND COMPETITIVE EXCELLENCE IN ROLLER DERBY. THIS PROGRAM HELPS OUR ATHLETES HONE THEIR SKILLS TO COMPETE AT A HIGH LEVEL, WHICH ATTRACTS FANS TO OUR EVENTS AND CONTRIBUTES TO OUR LEAGUE'S REPUTATION IN THE ROLLER DERBY COMMUNITY. OUR LEAGUE HAS FOUR MAIN TRAINING LEVELS, ALLOWING POINTS OF ACCESS BASED ON CURRENT SKILL AND EXPERIENCE. 1. PINKIES, 2. RAT LAB, MAUL RATS, MISCHIEF, 3. HOME TEAMS, 4. ALL STAR PROGRAM PINKIES IS AN INTRODUCTORY LEVEL FACILITATED BY LEAGUE MEMBERS THAT IS OPEN TO COMMUNITY MEMBERS, FOCUSING ON FOUNDATIONAL SKATING AND ROLLER DERBY SKILLS. RAT LAB, MAUL RATS AND MISCHIEF ARE THE NEXT LEVELS, WHERE THOSE CAN BEGIN WORKING ON CONTACT AND LEARNING HOW TO PLAY ROLLER DERBY IN ANTICIPATION OF JOINING A LEAGUE HOME TEAM. MISCHIEF IS FOR SKATERS QUALIFIED FOR THE HOME TEAM DRAFT AND IS ALSO A LEVEL WHERE TRANSFER SKATERS CAN JOIN OUR LEAGUE. THERE ARE THREE INTERLEAGUE HOME TEAMS WITH A LOCAL SEASON. THE ALL-STAR PROGRAM HAS A AND B PRIMARILY TRAVEL TEAMS THAT ARE INTERNATIONALLY RANKED DIVISION 1 LEVEL TEAMS. OUR LEAGUE DEVELOPS SKATERS AT EVERY LEVEL AND ACTIVELY WORKS TO CREATE AN INCLUSIVE ENVIRONMENT TO WELCOME NEW FOLKS TO OUR COMMUNITY. WE HAVE A SCHOLARSHIP AND HARDSHIP FUND THAT PROVIDES SUPPORT FOR THOSE WITH NEED FOR FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO BE ABLE TO HAVE ACCESS TO THE SPORT AND A GEAR LIBRARY WITH DONATED EQUIPMENT TO HELP THOSE OVERCOME THE INITIAL BARRIERS TO GETTING STARTED WITH ROLLER DERBY. APPROXIMATELY 170 SKATERS, OFFICIALS, AND VOLUNTEERS DIRECTLY BENEFIT FROM THIS PROGRAM.

WE ACTIVELY PROMOTE THE SPORT OF ROLLER DERBY THROUGH VARIOUS INITIATIVES. THIS INCLUDES ORGANIZING ROLLER DERBY CLINICS, COLLABORATING ON COMMUNITY EVENTS, AND FACILITATING DERBY GAMES AT A LOCAL AND INTERNATIONAL LEVEL OPEN TO THE PUBLIC FOR VIEWING. BY PROMOTING ROLLER DERBY, WE AIM TO INCREASE AWARENESS AND PARTICIPATION IN THE SPORT, FOSTERING A SENSE OF COMMUNITY AMONG ROLLER DERBY ENTHUSIASTS AND ENCOURAGING NEW TALENT TO JOIN OUR LEAGUE. THIS PROGRAM GENERATES REVENUE THROUGH TICKET SALES, MERCHANDISE, AND CONCESSIONS, WHICH HELPS SUSTAIN OUR LEAGUE AND FUND OUR OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES. IT ALSO SERVES AS A PLATFORM FOR PROMOTING ROLLER DERBY AND ENGAGING WITH OUR COMMUNITY.IN ADDITION TO BEING PUBLIC, THE GAMES ARE BROADCAST LIVE AND LATER MADE AVAILABLE ON YOUTUBE. MANY LOCAL AND INTERNATIONAL DERBY COMMUNITY INDIVIDUALS PARTICIPATE IN OR WATCH OUR ANNUAL EVENTS. LIVE SCREENING AND ARCHIVED ACCESS ON DEMAND INCREASES ACCESSIBILITY TO THE SPORT. VIDEOS WITH LEAGUE SKATERS AMASS FROM A COUPLE THOUSAND FOR HOME EVENTS AND SOME INTERNATIONAL GAMES GARNERING OVER 22K VIEWS. WE INTERACT WITH OUR COMMUNITY USING AN EMAILED NEWSLETTER, INSTAGRAM (OVER 7200 FOLLOWERS), AND FACEBOOK (OVER 48K FOLLOWERS).INDIVIDUALS WHO BENEFITED FROM THIS PROGRAM RANGE FROM A FEW HUNDRED TO OVER 20,000, DEPENDING ON THE EVENT AND MEDIUM OF INTERACTION. SMALLER EVENTS INCLUDE CLINICS AND FUNDRAISERS, WHILE OUR COMPETITIVE GAMES AND REGIONAL TOURNAMENTS CAN ATTRACT SEVERAL HUNDRED TO SEVERAL THOUSAND IN-PERSON AND REACH THOUSANDS, LIVE ON DEMAND.

MAKING A POSITIVE IMPACT IN OUR COMMUNITY IS FUNDAMENTAL TO OUR MISSION. WE ENGAGE IN COMMUNITY SERVICE AND OUTREACH ACTIVITIES, INCLUDING VOLUNTEERING AT LOCAL EVENTS, HOSTING CHARITY BOUTS, AND SUPPORTING YOUTH PROGRAMS RELATED TO ROLLER SPORTS. THIS PROGRAM BENEFITS THOSE DIRECTLY SERVED AND ENHANCES OUR LEAGUE'S REPUTATION AS A SOCIALLY RESPONSIBLE ORGANIZATION. IT ALLOWS US TO GIVE BACK TO THE COMMUNITY THAT SUPPORTS US AND FOSTERS GOODWILL. ROLLER DERBY IS MORE THAN JUST A SPORT; IT'S A POWERFUL VEHICLE FOR EMPOWERMENT AND COMMUNITY UPLIFTMENT. IN THE HEART OF THE ROLLER DERBY ARENA, INDIVIDUALS FIND NOT ONLY PHYSICAL STRENGTH BUT ALSO A SUPPORTIVE AND INCLUSIVE COMMUNITY THAT ENCOURAGES PERSONAL GROWTH AND SELF-CONFIDENCE.THROUGH ROLLER DERBY, INDIVIDUALS DISCOVER THEIR INNER STRENGTH AND RESILIENCE, PUSHING THE BOUNDARIES OF WHAT THEY ONCE THOUGHT POSSIBLE. THEY LEARN THE VALUE OF TEAMWORK, COMMUNICATION, AND PERSEVERANCE, ON AND OFF THE TRACK. ROLLER DERBY TRANSCENDS TRADITIONAL GENDER ROLES, OFFERING AN INCLUSIVE SPACE WHERE ANYONE CAN THRIVE, REGARDLESS OF AGE, BACKGROUND, OR IDENTITY.BEYOND THE ARENA, ROLLER DERBY LEAGUES OFTEN ENGAGE IN COMMUNITY OUTREACH, VOLUNTEERING, AND PHILANTHROPY. THEY WORK TIRELESSLY TO MAKE A POSITIVE IMPACT BY SUPPORTING LOCAL CHARITIES, PROMOTING WOMEN'S SPORTS, AND FOSTERING A SENSE OF BELONGING FOR EVERYONE.OUR COMMUNITY IMPACT PROGRAM REACHES APPROXIMATELY 3,000 PEOPLE ANNUALLY THROUGH VARIOUS OUTREACH ACTIVITIES AND COMMUNITY PARTICIPATION.

IN THE SPIRIT OF TRANSPARENCY AND ACCOUNTABILITY, THE LEAGUE CONSTANTLY STRIVES TO MAINTAIN CURRENT, ACCURATE, AND FAIR POLICIES WITHIN OUR ORGANIZING AND GOVERNING DOCUMENTS. STAYING UP-TO-DATE WITH OUR POLICIES IS ESSENTIAL TO ENSURE OUR ROLLER DERBY LEAGUE'S EFFICIENT AND EFFECTIVE OPERATION. TO FACILITATE THIS PROCESS, WE HAVE ESTABLISHED A DEDICATED COMMITTEE OF LEAGUE MEMBERS RESPONSIBLE FOR ASSESSING POTENTIAL POLICY CHANGES. THIS COMMITTEE THOROUGHLY REVIEWS PROPOSED CHANGES, CONSIDERS THEIR IMPLICATIONS, AND SEEKS INPUT FROM OUR LEAGUE MEMBERS TO ENSURE THAT THE POLICIES ALIGN WITH OUR CORE VALUES AND MISSION. ADDITIONALLY, WE UPHOLD A DEMOCRATIC APPROACH WHEN MAKING SIGNIFICANT CHANGES TO OUR ORGANIZING OR GOVERNING DOCUMENTS. EACH POLICY CHANGE IS SUBJECT TO A LEAGUE-WIDE VOTE, WHERE ALL ELIGIBLE LEAGUE MEMBERS CAN EXPRESS THEIR VIEWS AND CAST THEIR BALLOTS. IT'S IMPORTANT TO NOTE THAT OUR LEAGUE HAS A 75% VOTING PARTICIPATION REQUIREMENT TO REMAIN ACTIVE. THIS REQUIREMENT ENSURES THAT EACH VOTE RESULT ACCURATELY REPRESENTS THE LEAGUE'S CONSENSUS AND THAT DECISIONS ARE MADE WITH BROAD SUPPORT FROM OUR MEMBERSHIP. CHANGES TO OUR ORGANIZATIONAL DOCUMENTS INCLUDE UPDATING THE MEMBERSHIP ELIGIBILITY AND STATUS POLICY IN OCTOBER OF 2022. THIS POLICY CHANGE WAS IMPLEMENTED AFTER CAREFUL CONSIDERATION AND DISCUSSION WITHIN OUR LEAGUE. THIS POLICY STATES THE TYPES OF LEAGUE SKATER MEMBER STATUSES, SETS FORTH THE REQUIREMENTS AND BENEFITS FOR LEAGUE MEMBERSHIP, AND THE PROCESSES FOR MANAGING MEMBERS WHO DO NOT FULFILL THEIR REQUIREMENTS FOR MEMBERSHIP, TAKE A LEAVE OF ABSENCE, AND RETURN FROM AN ABSENCE. WE ARE COMMITTED TO A CULTURE OF CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT AND OPEN COMMUNICATION, AND WE WILL CONTINUE TO ASSESS AND ADJUST OUR POLICIES AS NECESSARY TO MEET THE EVOLVING NEEDS AND EXPECTATIONS OF OUR LEAGUE MEMBERS AND COMMUNITY.
